title: Employment by economic sector in South Africa 2009 to 2019
summary: The given chart is of multi-line type with 3 lines namely Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis represents Share of total employment and the x axis represents Year.
Overall Agriculture, Industry, and Services are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of total employment in descending order is: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Overall across the Year, Services mostly maintained the highest Share of total employment when compared to others with a mean value of 71.21, and it peaked at 2014.
After Services, Industry overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 23.7, peaking at 2009.
Agriculture mostly had the least Share of total employment with a mean value of 5.06, which peaked at 2015 with a value of 5.61.
